To summarize, the limitations of the individual systems are:
• the reliability of the V2P communication system is degraded due to the inaccuracy of the GPS data (Fig. 3a),
• the ability to detect pedestrians is limited by FOV of the sensors of perception systems (Fig. 3c),
• the ability to detect pedestrians is limited for the perception system if an obstacle blocks the line-of-sight to the pedestrian (Fig. 3d).

